Sentencas: Functional Sodium-doped cobalt oxide (Na0.6Co3O4, NCO) was incorporated to regulate and improve the electrochemical performance of La/Pr co-doped ceria (LCP) electrolytic materials with good operative stability, forming an p-n heterostructure electrolyte (LCP-NCO) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LTSOFC) application.
Titulo: Na0.6Co3O4- La/Pr co-Doped Ceria as Semiconductor-Ionic Heterostructure Material for Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: LCP-NCO is a new potential semiconductor-ionic material, achieving a maximum power density of 1075 mW cm(-2) along with a high open-circuit voltage of 1.061 V at 520 degrees C. Scanning electron microscopy combined with transmission electron microscopy unveiled the crystallographic microstructure of heterostructure interface between LCP and NCO.
Titulo: Na0.6Co3O4- La/Pr co-Doped Ceria as Semiconductor-Ionic Heterostructure Material for Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: Raman spectra and Fourier transform infrared spectroscopy spectra were analyzed to distinguish the functional groups and the vibrational properties.
Titulo: Na0.6Co3O4- La/Pr co-Doped Ceria as Semiconductor-Ionic Heterostructure Material for Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: Ultraviolet-visible absorption and ultraviolet photoelectron spectroscopy have determined the accurate band edge positions of LCP and NCO and p-n heterojunction nature.
Titulo: Na0.6Co3O4- La/Pr co-Doped Ceria as Semiconductor-Ionic Heterostructure Material for Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: Built-in electric field in semiconductor heterostructure and more oxygen vacancies created through the variation of Co3+/Co2+ ratio in LCP-NCO during the fuel cell test, contributed to the enhanced ionic transport.
Titulo: Na0.6Co3O4- La/Pr co-Doped Ceria as Semiconductor-Ionic Heterostructure Material for Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: Characteristic of competent conductivity of 0.26-0.42 S cm(-1) at 400 degrees C-520 degrees C, and the improved cell duration, revealed that the LCP-NCO as a hybrid oxygen ion and protonic conductor would be a potential electrolyte for LTSOFC.
Titulo: Na0.6Co3O4- La/Pr co-Doped Ceria as Semiconductor-Ionic Heterostructure Material for Fuel Cell Application
